cc:Work.dc:title: B Minor Scale (E Shape)

cc:Agent.dc:title: Created with CutyCapt by Björn Höhrmann

rdf:Bag.rdf:li: B Minor Scale, A B Minor scale consists of B, C#, D, E, F#, G and A notes. See diagrams at Standard Guitar.

cc:Work.dc:description: Start by assigning your fingers to the seventh, eighth, ninth and tenth frets. On the sixth string play a B on the seventh fret using your first finger, a C sharp on the ninth fret using your third finger and a D on the tenth fret using your fourth finger. On the fifth string play an E on the seventh fret using your first finger, an F sharp on the ninth fret using your third finger and a G on the tenth fret using your fourth finger. On the fourth string play an A on the seventh fret using your first finger and a B on the ninth fret using your third finger.
